      "objectEndDate": 1699,
      "medium": "Porcelain with overglaze color enamel and iron oxide rim (Arita ware)",
      "description": "This dish portrays Chinese scholar Zhou Dunyi—also known as Zhou Maoshu (1017–1073)—appreciating lotuses, a motif borrowed from Chinese porcelains. The ceramics painter of this work depicted Zhou seemingly appreciating both the lotus and the young lady with a lotus in the boat.",
