      "objectBeginDate": 1695,
      "objectEndDate": 1705,
      "medium": "Porcelain with underglaze blue and overglaze color enamel (Hizen ware, Nabeshima type)",
      "description": "The interior of this dish features clusters of reeds emerging from mist. The gradation of blue wash in the background suggests that the scene is set by still waters, perhaps the banks of a river or edge of a marsh. The celadon, or pale green glaze, evocative of mist or fog, contrasts visually with the reeds and water.",
