      "medium": "Porcelain with underglaze blue and overglaze color enamel and gold, with iron oxide rim (Arita ware)",
      "description": "This dish is inscribed with a poem from <em>The Gateless Gate</em>, a text compiled by Chinese Chan (Zen) master Wumen Huikai (1183–1260). The verse reads, “I always remember the spring in Jiangnan. Where the partridges sing; how fragrant the countless flowers!”",
