      "objectBeginDate": 1750,
      "objectEndDate": 1789,
      "medium": "porcelain with underglaze blue and molded decoration",
      "description": "The motif in the central medallion of this large dish depicts a knotted pine tree on the right with branches of pine needles forming triangular shapes resembling mountains in a distant landscape. Above and below the branches are three cloud bands in alternating light and dark washes of cobalt blue. In the foreground, a small blooming orchid reaches toward the left of the dish, balancing the gentle sway of the pine tree.",
